cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. It also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are commonly found in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Markov random fields suggests that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the application of the method to electron microscopic images suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
